<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="632" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">von Mumm</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-11-21"><hi rend="italic">November 21,
                                    1890</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. yon Mumm</hi>: I have the honor to
                            acknowledge the receipt of your personal note of the 18th instant,
                            informing me that Mr. Carl Eggert, the German member of the Samoan land
                            commission, would leave for Apia early in December.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>